        <name>avdtp_version</name>
        <qualifiedname>bt_a2dp_discover_param::avdtp_version</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
<para>The AVDTP version of the peer&apos;s A2DP sdp service. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Stack uses it to determine using get_all_cap or get_cap cmd. When both versions are v1.3 or bigger version, get_all_cap is used, otherwise get_cap is used. It is the same value of the avdtp sepcificaiton&apos;s version value. For example: 0x0103 means version 1.3 If the value is 0 (unknown), stack process it as less than v1.3 </para>
        </detaileddescription>
